                <problem>
        <title>P15</title>
        <p>
            A graph <m>G</m> is <em>bipartite</em> if the vertex set of <m>G</m> can be partitioned as <m>V=A\uplus B</m> in such a way that every edge in <m>G</m> has one endpoint in <m>A</m> and one in <m>B</m>.
            Prove that <m>G</m> is bipartite if and only if every cycle in <m>G</m> has an even number of edges.
        </p>
    </problem>
        <problem>
        <title>P16</title>
        <p>
            Suppose a tree <m>T</m> has exactly one vertex of degree <m>i</m> for each <m>2\leq i\leq m</m> and all other vertices have degree <m>1</m>.
            <ol>
                <li>
                    <p>
